I'm just... moving my lips!

17:03.564 --> 17:09.528
Uh, I'd like to start by saying
Maurice owes you an apology.

17:09.611 --> 17:15.451
You were supposed to protect us.
I'm traumatized here! I'm traumatized!

17:15.534 --> 17:21.081
I know. I forgot that after being horned,
my people would need a place to chill out.

17:21.165 --> 17:27.337
To get calm. Therefore,
I propose we create a No Conflict Zone.

17:27.421 --> 17:33.802
A nourishing womb that you can all crawl
into when things get just too horned.

17:33.886 --> 17:38.599
Where are we gonna find a womb that big?
We're all gonna die!

17:39.475 --> 17:45.439
Don't worry, I'm sure we can find
a womb big enough for all of you.

17:45.522 --> 17:47.066
I'm open to suggestions.

17:49.943 --> 17:55.657
Aw, you have got to be kidding me!
I've been kicked off my throne, again!

17:55.741 --> 17:58.535
Crystal clear salt water pool, eh?

17:58.619 --> 18:01.163
There's more dead things in
that pool than salt water.

18:01.246 --> 18:05.417
Clover's right. There's no way I could
put my Inflatable Pegasus Lounger

18:05.501 --> 18:09.838
or Floating Fiesta Island with
Dual Drink Cozies in there. Bummer.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.633
Well, I'm afraid that's everything,
Your Majesty.

18:12.716 --> 18:17.513
All the other kingdoms are still occupied.
We could, of course, uh, plunder.

18:17.596 --> 18:22.059
No. That was Koto's way. The chef
who steals the recipe of the thief

18:22.142 --> 18:25.562
will find his meal unfulfilling.
And he'll probably get the squirts.

18:25.646 --> 18:29.024
I, uh, believe they call it
the Madagascar shuffle.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.567
Right, shuffle.

18:30.651 --> 18:35.322
Hold on, what about the Mountain
Lemur's ancestral kingdom, eh

18:35.405 --> 18:37.616
Didn't you tell me it was the most
beautiful place you'd ever seen?

18:37.699 --> 18:41.620
Yes. My ancestral home
exudes a beauty so profound

18:41.703 --> 18:46.083
it can only be expressed in the grunts
and spasms of something yet unborn.

18:46.166 --> 18:50.921
Sadly, it has been abandoned for decades
and how could I be so stupid?

18:51.004 --> 18:55.425
We should just move back
into our old ancestral home.

18:55.509 --> 18:59.596
You truly are the worst
real estate broker ever.

18:59.680 --> 19:05.060
Such stupidity can be forgiven,
but not the waste of your precious time!

19:05.144 --> 19:07.604
Sage, I'm sure the Captain did
his best. There's no need to--

19:07.688 --> 19:09.481
I brought you an extra flogging stick.

19:09.565 --> 19:11.984
-Much thanks, my king.

19:15.904 --> 19:21.451
Xixi here, reporting live from the womb.
Uh, not a lot happening. It's kinda warm.

19:21.535 --> 19:26.331
Now how long do we... stay in here?

19:26.415 --> 19:32.171
You can't put no time limit on emotional
wounds. Those scars never heal!

19:32.254 --> 19:35.299
Zora

19:35.382 --> 19:41.555
Yes, Mort. When we go back to
stump to talk about family?

19:43.348 --> 19:46.393
Speaking of mistakes, where's Todd?

19:46.476 --> 19:49.062
My baby gets aggressive in tight spaces.

19:49.146 --> 19:52.274
Hey, something just grabbed my leg!

19:52.357 --> 19:54.902
-Todd!

19:54.985 --> 19:59.448
-Todd!
-We are doomed!

20:00.657 --> 20:03.327
I'm a two-time loser, Maurice.

20:03.410 --> 20:06.622
No disrespect, but you've lost
a few more times than that.

20:06.705 --> 20:09.208
What am I gonna do now? Wander the jungle,

20:09.291 --> 20:13.086
trying to sell myself as a trained
booty shaker who used to be a king?

20:13.170 --> 20:15.505
Nobody wants failure
twerking in front of them.

20:15.589 --> 20:21.470
All I wanted was to give my people peace
and kindness but all they wanted was-- That's it! Maurice, I know how
to fix this! All I have to do--

20:29.353 --> 20:32.481
King Julien, no! No!

20:32.814 --> 20:37.694
You can't take him now! Why, Frank

20:42.908 --> 20:47.663
That is it!
I am through with this kingdom!

20:47.746 --> 20:52.584
I'm starting my own sovereign nation
where the only voice I hear is--

20:52.668 --> 20:56.546
No! King Julien!

20:57.256 --> 21:03.053
Maurice, what did you do?
You were always jealous of him!

21:03.136 --> 21:06.932
I didn't do anything! It was the kingdom!
It was just too much for him.

21:07.015 --> 21:09.977
All he wanted was to do what
was best for his people.

21:10.060 --> 21:14.314
To give us the kingdom we'd always
dreamed of. To hear our voices.

21:14.982 --> 21:21.405
But instead, all anyone cared about was
having the loudest voice to complain.

21:21.488 --> 21:26.076
Who would want a kingdom of complainers?
Well, except maybe Hector.

21:26.159 --> 21:27.661
Not apologizing.

21:27.744 --> 21:32.082
We shouldn't be afraid of words or ideas.
Everyone gets hurt feelings

21:32.165 --> 21:35.085
and that's a good thing.
It means we're individuals.

21:35.168 --> 21:39.840
And that's how we make a great kingdom.
By learning from each other.

21:39.923 --> 21:43.385
And we should do it... for King Julien.

21:43.468 --> 21:46.346
It should have been me!

21:46.430 --> 21:50.767
Oh, Maurice, we must honor the King Julien

21:50.851 --> 21:54.229
by creating kingdom he proud of, no?

21:54.313 --> 21:59.860
The freak is right. We... owe him that.

21:59.943 --> 22:03.113
We begin today. Come, Mort.

22:03.196 --> 22:05.574
You know, I'm gonna hang back and--

22:07.492 --> 22:11.872
You may have been stubborn and wildly
inappropriate, King Julien...

22:12.414 --> 22:13.415
But you're still--

22:15.334 --> 22:21.048
Of course, Mo-Mo. That was what I figured
out. What do all good kingdoms have?

22:21.131 --> 22:24.676
Huh A martyr to unify them.

22:25.844 --> 22:29.973
Sometimes you just gotta go big.
And you totally sold it, Mo-Mo.

22:30.057 --> 22:33.560
I was grieving! What happens
when they find out you're alive?

22:33.643 --> 22:36.521
Ha! Please, in a few weeks
they'll have forgotten

22:36.605 --> 22:40.275
any of this even happened.
Julien 2.0, baby!

22:41.359 --> 22:46.239
♪ <i>A conflict-free life I believe we'll see</i>
<i>A kingdom of joy beneath the Baobab tree</i> ♪

22:46.323 --> 22:48.700
♪ <i>It's what we all need</i>
<i>And what we will flaunt</i> ♪

22:48.784 --> 22:51.328
♪ <i>A conflict-free life</i>
<i>Is what we all want</i> ♪

22:51.411 --> 22:56.374
♪ <i>No arguing</i>
<i>No opinions</i> ♪

22:56.458 --> 23:01.171
